  [1] In particular, if the stock falls then you might expect the dollar co=
st of stock borrow to fall.=20


  [2] Incidentally the value of these warrants is basically their intrinsic=
 value less borrow cost: There is not a ton of Black-Scholes time value in =
them, both because they are very in-the-money and because Trump Media can r=
edeem them (i.e. force exercise) pretty much as soon as they become exercis=
able.


  [3] Probably you want the borrowing to be non-recourse: That is, you post=
 $1 billion of stock to borrow $500 million, and if the stock goes down to =
$100 million, or zero, the banks can=E2=80=99t ask you for any more money; =
they can look only to the collateral to get their money back. Obviously the=
 banks will not like that so much, though there are ways to make them feel =
better. (Funded collars, etc.) But borrowing recourse against a meme stock =
is not *really* a good way to monetize it: If the stock goes to zero, you h=
ave to pay back the money!


  [4] I=20
have argued that just waiving the lock-up for him, so he could borrow again=
st his shares, would work fine too.


  [5] Also: =E2=80=9CPeople close to the Apollo bid said the private-equity=
 firm wouldn=E2=80=99t need additional debt financing to buy Paramount beca=
use its existing capital structure could be rolled into a new deal.=E2=80=
