<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are an activist hedge fund, I guess you=
 have two motivations:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You are, essentially, a value investo=
r: You buy companies that are cheap because they are mismanaged, and then y=
ou try to fix the mismanagement (by yelling at management, running proxy fi=
ghts, etc.) so the stock goes up.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=
You probably=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0</em>like conflict, right? You probably think=
 that you could do a better job of running the company than management does=
. You want to win proxy fights, get board seats, so that you can impose you=
r will on the company =E2=80=94=C2=A0and so that, <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34928529.256352/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJ=
nLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDYtMDEvaXQtcy1nb29kLXRvLXdpbi1hLXByb3=
h5LWZpZ2h0P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MDQyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX=
3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQwNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVm=
Zg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB67101da2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  in your=C2=A0<em>next=C2=A0=
</em>activist engagement</a>, the company will be scared of you and more li=
kely to do what you want.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You want to make money, and you want to win pr=
oxy fights. But you can make money while losing proxy fights, and you can l=
ose money while winning them.=C2=A0Which is more important? Would you rathe=
r have a good track record as a value investor or as a winner of proxy figh=
ts? If you ask an activist hedge fund manager about her successes, is she m=
ore likely to mention:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">the time she waged a proxy fight again=
st a public company, and the company=E2=80=99s management took the fight se=
riously and improved its operations in order to win the fight, with the res=
ult that (1) she lost the proxy fight and (2) the stock went up, or</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">the time she waged a proxy fight against =
a public company, and won, and got some board seats, but the company contin=
ued to languish with her in charge, and the stock went down?</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know, I am just asking the que=
stion. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34928529.25=
6352/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDQtMDQvZG=
lzbmV5LWNlby1zLWhlYWRhY2hlcy1hYm91bmQtZXZlbi1hZnRlci1kZWNpc2l2ZS1wcm94eS13Y=
XItd2luP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MDQyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3Nv=
dXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQwNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbef57ee6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Anyway</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On Wednesday at the annual meeting=
 of Walt Disney Co., shareholders elected all of management=E2=80=99s choic=
es to the board, turning aside the nomination of [activist investor Nelson]=
 Peltz, while also rejecting his ally, former Disney finance chief Jay Rasu=
lo, and a slate from another dissident group. Iger was reelected with 94% s=
upport, according to people familiar with the matter, who asked not to be i=
dentified discussing results that haven=E2=80=99t been announced publicly, =
while Peltz garnered 31% of the votes. In other words, a rout.</p></blockqu=
ote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/34928529.256352/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9idXNpbmVzcy9uZWxz=
b24tcGVsdHpzLWRpc25leS1jb25zb2xhdGlvbi1wcml6ZS1hLTMwMC1taWxsaW9uLWdhaW4tMzM=
4MjIyNjU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb6748056" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">also</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nelson Peltz may have suffered a bruising defe=
at in his proxy battle with Disney Wednesday, but the sting could be eased =
by a gain the activist has scored on the investment.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Peltz=E2=80=99s Trian Partners has made around=
 $300 million in profit on its 16-month investment, most of it on paper, ac=
cording to people familiar with the matter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The firm invested around $800 million in Disne=
y in 2022, buying much of its stake when shares were around $88 apiece. ...=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After subtracting the $25 million Trian expect=
ed to spend waging the campaign, the firm=E2=80=99s profit to date comes ou=
t to about $300 million.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is a roughly 40% return on the investment=
 over the period Trian has owned the shares, which is about equal to the S&=
amp;P 500=E2=80=99s return over the same period.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suppose the way to spin this is that Peltz f=
orced Disney to improve its operations and get serious about succession pla=
nning, which made the stock more valuable, so he lost the proxy fight.</p>
